w forms of exclusion. With Critique of Black Reason, Mbembe offers nothing less than a map of the world as it has been constituted through colonialism and racial thinking while providing the first glimpses of a more just future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aBlack peoplexRace identity. 0aBlacksxRace identity. 0aDifference (Philosophy) 0aDifference (Philosophy). 0aRace awarenessxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aRacexPhilosophy. 0aRacexSocial aspects. 0aRacism. 0aSlaveryxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aWhitesxRace identity. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aDubois, Laurent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106963490 cprintz978082236332340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822373230?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822373230423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822373230/original  a978-3-11-069634-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles